00:30:09,452 --> 00:30:13,573
and helping them talk through that and asking questions like,

558
00:30:13,573 --> 00:30:15,573
what's going right?

559
00:30:15,573 --> 00:30:17,074
What's getting in your way?

560
00:30:17,074 --> 00:30:20,854
And what are you learning about leading?

561
00:30:20,854 --> 00:30:24,075
Effective, meaningful one-on-ones.

562
00:30:24,075 --> 00:30:25,635
Mentorships.

563
00:30:25,635 --> 00:30:30,596
So we do not have a formal mentorship process at Blizzard.

564
00:30:30,596 --> 00:30:34,997
But we do like the idea of intentionally,

565
00:30:34,997 --> 00:30:37,757
there's that word again, pairing.

566
00:30:38,248 --> 00:30:39,169
people together.

567
00:30:39,169 --> 00:30:41,690
And we think about it in two ways.

568
00:30:41,690 --> 00:30:43,930
The traditional, like, senior person

569
00:30:43,930 --> 00:30:46,551
along with a less experienced person,

570
00:30:46,551 --> 00:30:50,393
or we're also starting to play with peer-to-peer mentorships.

571
00:30:50,393 --> 00:30:52,854
Always being very intentional.

